data.enText: to increase in degree or strength; to make sth increase in degree or strength

data.chText: 在夜间暴力活动加剧了。
反对派领袖加强了对政府的攻击。
data.enText: The opposition leader has intensified his attacks on the government.

simple_means.memory_skill: intens〔e〕强烈的 + ify 使… → 加强

example: His dislike for raw fish only deepened in Japan

tr: make more intense, stronger, or more marked
example: The efforts were intensified", "Her rudeness intensified his dislike for her
Pot smokers claim it heightens their awareness
This event only deepened my convictions

tr: make the chemically affected part of (a negative) denser or more opaque in order produce a stronger contrast between light and dark

value.def: If you intensify something or if it intensifies, it becomes greater in strength, amount, or degree.

example.ex: Britain is intensifying its efforts to secure the release of the hostages...
example.tran: 英国正加紧努力确保人质的获释。

example.ex: The conflict is almost bound to intensify...
Groups of refugees are on the move following intensified fighting in the region.
example.tran: 该地区战事加剧之后,大批难民开始逃离。

example.ex: The country was on the verge of collapse because of the intensification of violent rebel attacks.
example.tran: 由于叛乱分子的暴力袭击愈演愈烈,该国已处于崩溃的边缘。
